## TL;DR: Square Cushion Cut Diamond — What to Know First

**A square cushion cut diamond (L/W ratio 1.00–1.05) and a princess cut diamond produce nearly identical face-up footprints at any given carat weight — yet their optical character could not be more different, and that difference is The Square Illusion: buyers who have not seen both shapes in person often discover the wrong choice only after setting.** Filter your search to L/W ratio 1.00–1.05 before shopping any cushion diamond search; most Blue Nile results default to showing mixed ratios, and non-square cushions outnumber square in many inventory tiers. **→ Best entry pick:** [GIA 1.00ct G-VS1 Cushion Modified at $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — natural, GIA-certified, the market entry for square cushion at the G color tier.

**Priority:** Princess buyers who want rounded-corner softness should see both shapes in person before deciding — the face-up size looks similar, but the optical character does not. At G-VS quality, square cushion natural undercuts princess pricing (cushion from $1,891 vs princess from $2,141 at F-VS2); at D-VVS quality, cushion commands a 40–80% premium over princess — The Pillow Premium in action. Lab grown square cushion starts at approximately [$680](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for 1ct IGI — the same optical character as natural at 80% less cost.

