> "The Square Illusion is the most common source of shape regret I see in engagement ring consultations. A client comes in certain they want a princess cut because it's square and modern — they hold a square cushion next to it on the same hand and immediately say 'that's the one.' The face-up sizes are similar, the price per carat is comparable at G quality, but the cushion has a warmth and life to it that the princess cut, for all its precision, cannot replicate. I always make clients compare both in person before committing to either."
> — Farzana, Diamond Consultant

