The natural square cushion price-per-carat curve jumps sharply at the 1ct-to-2ct transition — a 1ct G-VS1 at $1,891/ct versus a 2ct F-VVS2 at $6,840/ct — because the scarcity and demand premium for 2ct+ natural cushion cuts increases non-linearly. At the 1ct G tier, square cushion natural diamonds deliver genuine value: [$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for a GIA-certified 1ct G-VS1 cushion modified is below the GIA 1ct G-VS2 princess at [$2,212](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961307?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — the cushion delivers the same visual impact at lower cost within the G quality range. This price relationship reverses at the D quality tier, a dynamic explained in full in The Pillow Premium section below.

Natural 2ct cushion diamonds require a significant budget step — entry at [$13,679 (F-VVS2)](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29359194?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) reflects real scarcity of GIA-certified 2ct natural cushion modified brilliant diamonds with high quality grades. Natural buyers at the 2ct tier should focus on G-VS quality where the price-to-appearance ratio is strongest: the spread between G-VS and F-VVS at 2ct is the widest in the cushion category, and G-VS natural cushions are visually identical to F-VVS under normal wearing conditions. Natural 3ct square cushion starts at [$32,692](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961123?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (G-VVS2) — the tier where lab grown makes the most compelling case.

