## Square Cushion Cut Lab Grown Diamond

The square cushion cut lab grown diamond delivers the same pillow shape, the same soft-corner aesthetic, and the same crushed ice sparkle character as natural — at 70–90% lower cost. An [IGI 1.5ct E-VVS2 lab cushion at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) provides better measurable quality than most natural 1ct cushion options at roughly half the price of a comparable natural 1.5ct stone. For buyers who want maximum face-up size in the square cushion outline without the natural provenance premium, lab grown is the clear choice at every budget level.

IGI certification is the correct choice for lab grown square cushion cuts — the same grading scale as GIA, at 40–140% lower certification cost that passes through directly to the buyer's stone price. A GIA-certified lab cushion at the same specifications as an IGI-certified lab cushion will cost significantly more for an identical stone; the GIA lab certification premium delivers no buyer benefit since lab grown resale value is near-zero regardless of which lab issued the certificate. For natural cushion diamonds, GIA is the only correct recommendation; for lab grown, IGI is correct at every carat tier.

