## The Pillow Premium

**The Pillow Premium is the quality-grade-dependent price relationship between square cushion cut diamonds and princess cut diamonds — and it runs in opposite directions at different quality tiers, creating a counterintuitive buying dynamic that most cushion shoppers discover only after they have begun comparing specific stones.** At the market sweet spot (G-VS quality, 1ct), square cushion natural undercuts princess: GIA 1ct G-VS1 cushion at [$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) versus GIA 1ct G-VS2 princess at [$2,212](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961307?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — cushion is 15% cheaper at a higher clarity grade. At the D-VVS tier, the relationship inverts sharply: GIA 1ct D-VVS1 cushion at [$4,873](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29255833?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) versus GIA 1ct D-VS2 princess at [$2,423](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26462136?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — cushion commands a premium exceeding 100% at the top color tier.

The mechanic behind The Pillow Premium is diamond rough yield. A princess cut is cut from octahedral rough with near-zero material loss — the square corners of the princess align with the natural crystal structure, preserving the most expensive portions of the rough. A cushion cut's rounded corners require the cutter to discard portions of high-value rough to produce the soft-corner geometry; at G quality this waste is modest, but at D color it is pure D-grade rough being discarded — and that waste cost passes directly to the buyer.

The Pillow Premium has a clear practical buying rule: if your budget is at G-VS quality, the square cushion is the better value of the two shapes — more character for less money. If your budget targets D-VVS quality and you are choosing between shapes for the same total spend, the princess delivers more D-grade carat weight per dollar than the cushion does at this tier. The cushion's rounded corners are genuinely more beautiful to buyers who prefer the pillow aesthetic — but The Pillow Premium quantifies exactly how much that beauty costs above the G quality threshold.

