## Square Cushion Cut Diamond Ring

The square cushion cut diamond ring is the most traditional engagement ring configuration for the cushion shape — the balanced L/W ratio sits centered in any setting style, and the soft corners create a natural visual softening of the stone-to-setting junction that elongated cushions cannot replicate as evenly. Setting selection for a square cushion cut follows different priorities than elongated cushions: because there is no dominant axis to emphasize, the setting's visual weight distributes evenly around the stone, making both solitaire and halo styles equally effective. This visual balance is the primary reason square cushion cuts are the most versatile cushion shape in engagement ring design.

Four-prong solitaire settings are the most popular choice for square cushion cut diamonds because they expose the maximum face-up area, position prongs symmetrically at the stone's corners, and allow the soft-corner geometry to be visible from all angles. The prong-at-corners configuration for a square cushion aligns with the stone's geometry naturally — four equal prongs at four equal corners — in a way that looks deliberately designed rather than incidentally placed. The [Petite Solitaire 14K White Gold at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (1,020 reviews) is the most popular setting for square cushion cuts at Blue Nile and works with stones from 1ct to 2ct without visual imbalance.

Eight-prong settings — two prongs at each corner rather than one — are particularly well-suited to square cushion cuts because the doubled prongs mirror the soft-corner geometry and reduce single-prong stress on each corner. For buyers at 2ct and above, an eight-prong setting provides both corner security and a visual doubling of the corner definition that makes the pillow shape more pronounced. For the full ring-building guide covering setting styles across all square cushion ring budgets, see [Cushion Cut Diamond Solitaire Ring](/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-ring).

