## Square Cushion Cut Halo Ring

The square cushion cut halo engagement ring is one of the most visually effective shape-setting combinations in the diamond category — the halo's surrounding diamonds trace the cushion's soft-corner outline and amplify the pillow geometry, creating an effect that no other shape-setting pairing produces as naturally. A 1ct square cushion in a cushion halo setting reads as a 1.3–1.5ct solitaire face-up due to the halo's visual contribution to the stone's apparent diameter. This is why the halo setting has been particularly dominant for square cushion buyers: the soft corners of the cushion align with the rounded halo head, creating a unified pillow-shaped visual boundary rather than the angular junction that occurs when a halo is placed around a princess cut.

The cushion halo design choice involves one key decision: a matching-shaped halo head (rounded square that mirrors the cushion's corners) versus a round halo (circular ring of diamonds surrounding the square cushion). The matching cushion halo head preserves the pillow shape and adds corner definition while amplifying the soft-corner geometry. The round halo reduces the square appearance and makes the stone read more as a round diamond — preferred by some buyers — but for buyers who specifically chose the square cushion for its soft-corner outline, the matching head is always the correct choice.

The most popular Blue Nile cushion halo settings start from [$1,780](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?style=halo&ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — a complete 1ct natural halo ring starting from [$3,671](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?style=halo&ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ([GIA 1ct G-VS1 at $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + halo setting from $1,780). For the full halo setting breakdown covering specific designs, prong types, and complete price builds across all budgets, see [Halo Cushion Cut Diamond Ring](/halo-cushion-cut-diamond-ring).

## Square vs Elongated Cushion Cut

**The square versus elongated cushion cut decision is one of the most consequential shape choices in the cushion diamond category — and it is entirely a visual preference decision with no difference in optical quality, sparkle mechanism, or base price per carat.** Both sub-variants use the same cushion modified brilliant facet structure, both produce the same distributed crushed ice sparkle character, and both are available in identical quality grades across the same carat range at comparable prices. What differs is the face-up outline on the finger and the resulting ring aesthetic.

The square cushion (L/W 1.00–1.05) sits balanced and centered on the finger: equal visual weight in all directions, a compact pillow geometry, and a ring that reads as a centered statement. The elongated cushion (L/W 1.15–1.25) runs diagonally across the finger: a length-to-width contrast that makes the finger appear longer and the ring appear larger than a same-carat square cushion — approximately 8–12% more apparent face-up length. At any given carat weight, the elongated cushion provides more apparent face-up size efficiency in exchange for the compact pillow look of the square.

