The pricing at equivalent quality is essentially the same between square and elongated cushion cuts at G-VS quality — a square 1ct cushion G-VS1 and an elongated 1ct cushion G-VS1 will be within 5% of each other in price at comparable dimensions. For the complete guide to elongated cushion cut lab grown diamonds covering The Lab Sovereign pricing tier at 3ct+, see [Elongated Cushion Cut Lab Grown Diamond](/elongated-cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond).

## Square Cushion Cut Solitaire

The square cushion cut solitaire places all visual emphasis on the cushion's face-up outline — the soft corners, the pillow depth, and the crushed ice sparkle pattern are the entire ring, without competition from surrounding halo diamonds or side stones. For buyers who specifically want the cushion's optical character in its purest form, the solitaire is the uncompromised choice. It is also the easiest setting for the buyer to upgrade the center stone later if budget allows, since solitaire head replacements are straightforward.

Prong count matters significantly in square cushion solitaires. Four prongs at the four corners is the standard and most popular configuration: it exposes maximum face-up area, aligns prongs symmetrically with the cushion geometry, and makes the soft corners visible at all viewing angles. For square cushion cuts at 2ct and above, eight prongs (two per corner) provides additional corner security and creates a more visually substantial stone-to-setting junction that scales better with larger stone weight.

Metal selection for square cushion solitaires follows color-grade logic: D–F colorless grades are best in white gold or platinum, where the cool metal maximizes contrast and produces the cleanest expression of the pillow shape. G–H color grades pair with yellow gold to neutralize warmth perception across the cushion's wide face-up table. For yellow gold solitaire recommendations, see [Cushion Cut Diamond Engagement Ring](/cushion-cut-diamond-engagement-ring).

